    <thetext>In section &quot;11.2 WhiteSpace&quot;, table 27 lists the ECMAScript whitespace characters, and goes on to state that &quot;ECMAScript implementations must recognize all of the white space characters defined in Unicode 5.1&quot;.

However the table doesn&apos;t account for U+0085 &quot;NEXT LINE (NEL)&quot; which is defined as White_Space in Unicode 5.1 (see http://www.unicode.org/Public/5.1.0/ucd/PropList.txt ), and is not covered by the &quot;Other Category Zs&quot; row in table 27 (as it is in category &quot;Cc&quot;).</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
